  {
   "question": "Where does Holy Priest Phase 4 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 335 top-ranked Holy Priest healing parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 4 (Zul'Aman), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Holy Priest items in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Boots of the Divine Light (88%), Swiftheal Wraps (72%), Naaru-Blessed Life Rod (71%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Zul'Aman."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Holy Priest use in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "Insightful Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Holy Priest need in Phase 4?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Renewal on head, Greater Inscription of Faith on shoulders, Golden Spellthread on legs and Enchant Weapon - Major Healing on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Renewal comes from Quartermaster — Hellfire Peninsula."
